                <!-- =========================
                        HOME
                ========================= -->


                <section id="home" class="hero">


                        <div class="hero-content">


                                <h1 class="reveal">

                                        Can Gene Expression
                                        <br>
                                        Help Us Understand
                                        <br>
                                        Colon Cancer?

                                </h1>



                                <p class="reveal">

                                Using microarray analysis to identify
                                differences in gene expression between
                                healthy and cancer tissue.

                                </p>



                                <a onclick="scrollToSection('research')" 
                                class="button reveal">

                                Start Exploring ↓

                                </a>


                        </div>


                </section>







                <!-- =========================
                        PART 1 RESEARCH
                ========================= -->


                <section id="research" class="chapter">



                <h1 class="chapter-title reveal">

                PART 1

                <br>

                RESEARCH

                </h1>



                <p class="chapter-subtitle reveal">

                Understanding the biological problem
                before analyzing the data.

                </p>







                <!-- =========================
                        SECTION 1
                ========================= -->


                <section class="subsection">


                        <h2 class="reveal">

                        Why Does This Matter?

                        </h2>



                        <p class="reveal">

                        Colon cancer is one of the most common
                        types of cancer worldwide. It develops
                        when cells in the colon accumulate
                        changes that disrupt normal growth
                        and function.

                        </p>



                        <div class="stats">



                                <div class="stat reveal">

                                        <h3>

                                        1.9 Million

                                        </h3>

                                        <p>

                                        New cases of colorectal cancer
                                        each year worldwide.

                                        </p>

                                </div>




                                <div class="stat reveal">

                                        <h3>

                                        900,000+

                                        </h3>

                                        <p>

                                        Deaths caused by colorectal cancer
                                        each year.

                                        </p>

                                </div>




                                <div class="stat reveal">

                                        <h3>

                                        #3

                                        </h3>

                                        <p>

                                        Most common cancer worldwide.

                                        </p>

                                </div>



                        </div>





                        <h3 class="reveal">
                        Who is most affected?
                        </h3> // NOTE MAKE SPACING BIGGER


                        <div class="center-content reveal">

                        <p>

                        Colon cancer predominantly affects older
                        adults, especially people over the age
                        of 50. However, younger cases are
                        increasing.

                        </p>


                        <p>

                        Risk factors include:

                        </p>


                        <ul>

                        <li>
                        High intake of processed meats
                        </li>

                        <li>
                        Low intake of fruits and vegetables
                        </li>

                        <li>
                        Sedentary lifestyle
                        </li>

                        <li>
                        Obesity
                        </li>

                        <li>
                        Family history of colon cancer
                        </li>

                        </ul>

                        </div>





                        <h3 class="symptoms-title reveal">

                        Symptoms

                        </h3>



                        <div class="center-content reveal">

                        <p>
                        Common symptoms include:
                        </p>

                        <ul>

                        <li>Diarrhea or constipation</li>

                        <li>Blood in stool</li>

                        <li>Abdominal pain</li>

                        <li>Unexplained weight loss</li>

                        <li>Fatigue and low iron levels</li>

                        </ul>

                        </div>



                        <p class="reveal highlight center-text">

                        Many people show no symptoms
                        during early stages, making detection
                        difficult.

                        </p>





                        </section>





                        <!-- =========================
                        EARLY DETECTION
                        ========================= -->


                <section class="subsection">



                <h2 class="reveal">

                Why Early Diagnosis Matters

                </h2>



                <p class="reveal">

                Early detection greatly improves the
                chance of successful treatment.
                Treatments are often more effective
                before the cancer spreads.

                </p>



                <div class="card-grid">



                <div class="card reveal">

                <h3>

                Screening

                </h3>


                <p>

                Regular screening can detect
                cancer before symptoms appear.

                </p>


                </div>




                <div class="card reveal">

                <h3>

                Surgery

                </h3>


                <p>

                Often used when cancer is detected
                at earlier stages.

                </p>


                </div>




                <div class="card reveal">

                <h3>

                Treatment Options

                </h3>


                <p>

                Includes chemotherapy, radiation,
                targeted therapy, and immunotherapy.

                </p>


                </div>



                </div>



                </section>





                <!-- =========================
                END OF PART 1
                ========================= -->

                <!-- =========================
                WHY GENE CHANGES MATTER
                ========================= -->


                <section class="subsection">


                <h2 class="reveal">

                Why Do Gene Changes Happen During Cancer?

                </h2>



                <p class="reveal">

                Cancer occurs when changes in DNA disrupt
                the normal instructions that control how
                cells grow, divide, and repair themselves.

                </p>



                <p class="reveal">

                These changes can cause genes involved
                in cell growth, DNA repair, and immune
                response to become incorrectly regulated.

                </p>



                <div class="card-grid">


                <div class="card reveal">

                <h3>
                Normal Cell
                </h3>

                <p>

                Genes controlling growth and repair
                are properly regulated.

                </p>

                </div>



                <div class="card reveal">

                <h3>
                Cancer Cell
                </h3>

                <p>

                Some genes become overactive while
                others become inactive, changing
                cell behavior.

                </p>

                </div>



                </div>



                </section>







                <!-- =========================
                GENE EXPRESSION
                ========================= -->


                <section class="subsection">



                <h2 class="reveal">

                What Is Gene Expression?

                </h2>



                <p class="reveal">

                Almost every cell in the human body
                contains the same DNA. However,
                different cells use different genes,
                allowing them to perform specialized
                functions.

                </p>



                <p class="reveal">

                Genes are sections of DNA that contain
                instructions for creating RNA and
                proteins. The process of using these
                instructions is called gene expression.

                </p>




                <!-- DNA FLOW ANIMATION -->


                <div class="gene-flow">


                <div class="gene-box reveal">

                DNA

                <span>

                Stored genetic instructions

                </span>

                </div>



                <div class="arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>



                <div class="gene-box reveal">

                mRNA

                <span>

                A copied version of the instructions

                </span>

                </div>



                <div class="arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>



                <div class="gene-box reveal">

                Protein

                <span>

                Molecules that perform functions
                inside cells

                </span>

                </div>



                <div class="arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>



                <div class="gene-box reveal">

                Cell Behavior

                <span>

                Growth, repair, and function

                </span>

                </div>


                </div>



                </section>







                <section class="subsection">


                <h2 class="reveal">

                What Does It Mean For A Gene To Be
                "Turned On" Or "Turned Off"?

                </h2>



                <div class="card-grid">


                <div class="card reveal">


                <h3>

                Gene Turned On

                </h3>


                <p>

                A more active gene produces more
                mRNA and more proteins.

                </p>


                <p class="highlight">

                Higher gene expression

                </p>



                </div>





                <div class="card reveal">


                <h3>

                Gene Turned Off

                </h3>


                <p>

                A less active gene produces less
                mRNA and fewer proteins.

                </p>


                <p class="highlight">

                Lower gene expression

                </p>


                </div>



                </div>



                <p class="reveal">

                In cancer cells, normal gene regulation
                can become disrupted. Some genes may
                become unusually active while others
                become less active.

                </p>



                <p class="reveal">

                By comparing gene expression patterns
                between healthy and tumor tissue, we
                can identify these differences.

                </p>



                </section>







                <!-- =========================
                MICROARRAY
                ========================= -->


                <section class="subsection">



                <h2 class="reveal">

                How Can We Measure Gene Expression?

                </h2>



                <p class="reveal">

                DNA microarrays are a technology used
                to measure the expression levels of
                thousands of genes at the same time.

                </p>



                <p class="reveal">

                They allow scientists to determine which
                genes are highly active and which genes
                have low activity.

                </p>




                <h3 class="microarray-title reveal">

                How Does A DNA Microarray Work?

                </h3>





                <div class="pipeline">



                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                1.
                <br>

                Collect Tissue Samples

                <p>

                Healthy and cancer samples are collected
                for comparison.

                </p>

                </div>



                <div class="pipeline-arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>



                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                2.
                <br>

                Extract RNA

                <p>

                RNA provides information about which
                genes are being used.

                </p>

                </div>



                <div class="pipeline-arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>




                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                3.
                <br>

                Convert RNA Into cDNA

                <p>

                RNA is converted into a more stable form
                called complementary DNA.

                </p>

                </div>




                <div class="pipeline-arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>



                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                4.
                <br>

                Add Fluorescent Labels

                <p>

                Labels allow the amount of genetic
                material to be detected.

                </p>

                </div>




                <div class="pipeline-arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>




                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                5.
                <br>

                Hybridize To Microarray Chip

                <p>

                cDNA binds to matching DNA probes
                on the chip.

                </p>

                </div>




                <div class="pipeline-arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>




                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                6.
                <br>

                Analyze Expression Data

                <p>

                Computational methods identify genes
                that differ between samples.

                </p>

                </div>



                </div>



                </section>







                <!-- =========================
                RESEARCH QUESTION
                ========================= -->


                <section class="question-section">



                <h2 class="reveal">

                Our Research Question

                </h2>



                <p class="research-question reveal">

                Which genes are expressed differently
                in colon cancer compared with healthy
                colon tissue?

                </p>



                <p class="reveal">

                By measuring gene expression levels,
                we can compare healthy and diseased
                samples to identify important genetic
                changes.

                </p>



                <div class="transition reveal">


                <h1>

                PART 2

                <br>

                ALGORITHM

                </h1>


                <p>

                How can we use data analysis to answer
                our research question?

                </p>


                </div>



                </section>

                <!-- =========================
                        PART 2 ALGORITHM
                ========================= -->


                <section id="algorithm" class="chapter">


                <h1 class="chapter-title reveal">

                PART 2

                <br>

                ALGORITHM

                </h1>


                <p class="chapter-subtitle reveal">

                Using computational methods to identify
                differences in gene expression.

                </p>






                <!-- =========================
                DATASET
                ========================= -->


                <section class="subsection">


                <h2 class="reveal">

                Our Dataset

                </h2>


                <p class="reveal">

                We analyzed an Affymetrix microarray
                dataset containing gene expression data
                from healthy colon tissue and colon
                cancer samples.

                </p>


                <p class="reveal">

                Each sample contains measurements for
                thousands of genes, allowing us to compare
                gene activity between healthy and tumor
                tissue.

                </p>


                </section>






                <!-- =========================
                COMPUTATIONAL PIPELINE
                ========================= -->


                <section class="subsection">


                <h2 class="reveal">

                Computational Method

                </h2>



                <div class="pipeline">



                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                Raw Microarray Data

                <p>

                Expression measurements collected from
                patient samples.

                </p>

                </div>



                <div class="pipeline-arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>




                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                Data Cleaning

                <p>

                Remove missing or unusable data and
                prepare the dataset for analysis.

                </p>

                </div>



                <div class="pipeline-arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>



                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                Normalization

                <p>

                Adjust expression values so samples can
                be accurately compared.

                </p>

                </div>



                <div class="pipeline-arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>



                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                Differential Expression Analysis

                <p>

                Find genes with significant differences
                between healthy and cancer samples.

                </p>

                </div>



                </div>


                </section>







                <!-- =========================
                LIMMA
                ========================= -->


                <section class="subsection">


                <h2 class="reveal">

                Statistical Analysis: Limma

                </h2>


                <p class="reveal">

                Limma is a statistical method designed
                for analyzing gene expression data.

                </p>


                <p class="reveal">

                It uses linear models to compare gene
                expression levels between groups and
                determines which genes show significant
                changes.

                </p>



                <div class="card-grid">


                <div class="card reveal">

                <h3>

                Fold Change

                </h3>

                <p>

                Measures how much gene expression
                changes between cancer and healthy
                samples.

                </p>


                </div>



                <div class="card reveal">


                <h3>

                p-value

                </h3>


                <p>

                Determines whether the observed change
                is statistically significant.

                </p>


                </div>



                <div class="card reveal">


                <h3>

                Adjusted p-value

                </h3>


                <p>

                Corrects for testing thousands of genes
                at the same time.

                </p>


                </div>



                </div>



                </section>







                <!-- =========================
                WELCH T TEST
                ========================= -->


                <section class="subsection">


                <h2 class="reveal">

                Welch's t-test

                </h2>


                <p class="reveal">

                Welch's t-test is another statistical
                method used to compare the average
                expression levels between two groups.

                </p>


                <p class="reveal">

                We compared the results from Welch's
                t-test with Limma to see whether both
                methods identified similar changes.

                </p>



                </section>







                <!-- =========================
                FLOWCHART
                ========================= -->


                <section class="subsection">


                <h2 class="reveal">

                Analysis Workflow

                </h2>



                <div class="flowchart">


                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                Microarray Data

                </div>


                <div class="pipeline-arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>


                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                Normalization

                </div>


                <div class="pipeline-arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>


                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                Differential Expression Testing

                </div>



                <div class="pipeline-arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>



                <div class="split-results">


                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                Limma

                </div>


                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                Welch's t-test

                </div>


                </div>



                <div class="pipeline-arrow reveal">

                ↓

                </div>



                <div class="split-results">


                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                Volcano Plot

                <br>

                Heatmap

                </div>


                <div class="pipeline-step reveal">

                Volcano Plot

                <br>

                Heatmap

                </div>


                </div>



                </div>



                </section>







                <!-- =========================
                RESULTS
                ========================= -->


                <section id="results" class="chapter">


                <h1 class="chapter-title reveal">

                RESULTS

                </h1>


                <p class="chapter-subtitle reveal">

                What did our analysis reveal?

                </p>







                <!-- LIMMA RESULTS -->


                <section class="subsection">


                <h2 class="reveal">

                Limma Results

                </h2>



                <div class="image-card reveal">


                <h3>

                Volcano Plot

                </h3>


                <img src="images/limma_volcano.png"
                alt="Limma Volcano Plot">


                </div>




                <div class="image-card reveal">


                <h3>

                Heatmap

                </h3>


                <img src="images/limma_heatmap.png"
                alt="Limma Heatmap">


                </div>




                </section>








                <!-- T TEST RESULTS -->


                <section class="subsection">


                <h2 class="reveal">

                Welch's t-test Results

                </h2>



                <div class="image-card reveal">


                <h3>

                Volcano Plot

                </h3>


                <img src="images/ttest_volcano.png"
                alt="Welch t-test Volcano Plot">


                </div>





                <div class="image-card reveal">


                <h3>

                Heatmap

                </h3>


                <img src="images/ttest_heatmap.png"
                alt="Welch t-test Heatmap">


                </div>




                </section>








                <section class="subsection">


                <h2 class="reveal">

                Why Do These Results Matter?

                </h2>



                <p class="reveal">

                The identified genes show differences
                between healthy and cancer tissue.

                </p>



                <p class="reveal">

                These genes may help researchers discover
                biomarkers for colon cancer and better
                understand how tumors develop.

                </p>



                <p class="reveal">

                While gene expression analysis will not
                replace current cancer screening methods,
                it can support personalized oncology after
                diagnosis.

                </p>



                <p class="reveal">

                Microarray analysis can help predict tumor
                behavior, guide treatment decisions, and
                uncover pathways that may lead to future
                cancer therapies.

                </p>



                </section>



                </section>








                <!-- =========================
                CONCLUSION
                ========================= -->


                <section id="conclusion" class="chapter conclusion">


                <h1 class="chapter-title reveal">

                CONCLUSION

                </h1>


                <p class="research-question reveal">

                Gene expression analysis provides a way
                to understand how colon cancer changes
                cell behavior.

                </p>



                <p class="reveal">

                By comparing healthy and cancer tissue,
                we can identify genes that are expressed
                differently and gain insight into the
                biology of the disease.

                </p>



                <h2 class="reveal">

                Thank You

                </h2>



                </section>





                <script src="script.js"></script>


        </body>

</html>